<p style="text-align: left;" data-mce-style="text-align: left;"><strong>Ajmodadi Churna</strong> is typically used in Ayurvedic medicine to support digestion, alleviate gastrointestinal discomfort, reduce inflammation, promote joint health and manage various other health conditions.</p>
<p data-mce-fragment="1"><noimg style="float: none;" nosrc="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0570/9070/3556/files/4_0edc038f-5505-4a88-ac69-45463945ed8f_2048x2048.jpg?v=1680348454" data-mce-style="float: none;" data-mce-nosrc="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0570/9070/3556/files/4_0edc038f-5505-4a88-ac69-45463945ed8f_2048x2048.jpg?v=1680348454"></p>
<p style="text-align: left;" data-mce-style="text-align: left;">1. Ajmodadi Churna is commonly used to improve digestion, relieve gas and bloating, flatulence and alleviate abdominal pain.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;" data-mce-style="text-align: left;">2. It is also believed to have a mild laxative effect and may help to regulate bowel movements.</p>
